    "Other possibilities are mentioned in \"Alternative surveillance approaches based on data mines\" section.",
    "Continuous, active, and comprehensive monitoring of health and scientific knowledge is necessary for broadspectrum surveillance (Morris et al. 2022).",
    "Currently, these approaches are mostly manual and focus on a specific subject.",
    "However, keeping knowledge in a field up to date is more challenging than ever.",
    "Knowledge is evolving rapidly, is obtained from sources and processes that are more or less reliable, and essential signals can be drowned out by a high degree of information redundancy over an increasing diversity of subjects making it beyond human capacities to keep abreast."
